         <abstract id="aspace_037a2fcaffcbf36ad5fecb5c13e337e9">The papers consist of nine volumes, six of which contain records of claims for pensions made by Civil War veterans from Connecticut. The remaining volumes contain accounts related to John Graves Chapman's insurance business, a letterbook (ca. 1866-1879), and a collection of mounted postmarks.</abstract>
